I see no reason to have any new laws on cryptography (except perhaps a
full right-to-privacy amendment).

Crypto has been used in espionage cases for a LONG time.

Crypto has been used by criminals for a LONG time.

[see Kahn's "Codebreakers" for some stories.]

The country is still here -- functioning nicely, thank you.

